# SqliteMcp project rules

## Architecture

- Stdio MCP server using `ModelContextProtocol` + `Microsoft.Data.Sqlite`.
- All connections go through singleton `SqliteConnectionManager` (keyed dictionary).
- Tools in `Tools/` stay thin; quoting/validation/SQL execution live in `Sql/`.

## Connection rules

- Default key name: `default`.
- Startup `--default-db` / `DefaultDbPath` stores path only; do not open until first need or `open_db`.
- No `connectionKey` + default configured → lazy-open `default`.
- No `connectionKey` + no default → error.
- With `connectionKey` → dictionary lookup only; missing key → error.
- `open_db`: same key + different path → error; same path → reuse.
- `close_db` / `close_all` dispose connections to release file locks; keep configured default path after close.

## Tool conventions

- Optional `connectionKey` on every DB tool.
- Return pretty-printed JSON strings from tools.
- Reject empty `conditions` on update/delete.
- Validate table/column names for CRUD; quote identifiers.
- Never log to stdout; use stderr logging only (`LogToStandardErrorThreshold`).

## When adding tools

- Mark types with `[McpServerToolType]` and methods with `[McpServerTool]`.
- Resolve connections via `SqliteConnectionManager.GetConnection` / `Open` / `Close`.
- Keep descriptions accurate; warn clearly on destructive tools (`close_all`).
